          <unittitle>Organizational Affiliations <unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1944/1971">1944-1971</unitdate></unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Organizational Affiliations series (1944-1971; 1 linear feet) details Van Tyne's leadership and membership roles within several civic organizations in the Washtenaw County area. The materials in this series reflect Van Tyne's concern with issues of child care, juvenile delinquency, and treatment of juvenile offenders in area court procedures. Administrative papers such as minutes and membership rosters and correspondence related to organizations such as Planned Parenthood, the James Foster Foundation, the Juvenile Court Advisory Council, and the Michigan Council on Women in Business and Industry serve to document Van Tyne's various roles and responsibilities throughout three decades as a civic leader in Ann Arbor.</p>
        </scopecontent>
